#: ../../library/asyncio-task.rst:137
msgid "Awaitables"
msgstr "AguardûÀveis"

#: ../../library/asyncio-task.rst:139
msgid ""
"We say that an object is an **awaitable** object if it can be used in an :"
"keyword:`await` expression.  Many asyncio APIs are designed to accept "
"awaitables."
msgstr ""
"Dizemos que um objeto ûˋ um objeto **aguardûÀvel** se ele pode ser usado em "
"uma expressûÈo :keyword:`await`. Muitas APIs asyncio sûÈo projetadas para "
"aceitar aguardûÀveis."

#: ../../library/asyncio-task.rst:143
msgid ""
"There are three main types of *awaitable* objects: **coroutines**, "
"**Tasks**, and **Futures**."
msgstr ""
"Existem trûˆs tipos principais de objetos *aguardûÀveis*: **corrotinas**, "
"**Tarefas**, e **Futuros**."

#: ../../library/asyncio-task.rst:149
msgid ""
"Python coroutines are *awaitables* and therefore can be awaited from other "
"coroutines::"
msgstr ""
"Corrotinas Python sûÈo *aguardûÀveis* e portanto podem ser aguardadas a partir "
"de outras corrotinas::"

#: ../../library/asyncio-task.rst:152
msgid ""
"import asyncio\n"
"\n"
"async def nested():\n"
"    return 42\n"
"\n"
"async def main():\n"
"    # Nothing happens if we just call \"nested()\".\n"
"    # A coroutine object is created but not awaited,\n"
